The paper discusses description logics, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and knowledge representation (cs.AI). It also focuses on the DL-Lite family, which is a subset of description logics that has been used in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of inference, which is a topic in logic and complexity theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses conceptual modeling formalisms, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
